org.zaproxy.zap.extension.httpsessions
Class HttpSession

java.lang.Object
  org.zaproxy.zap.extension.httpsessions.HttpSession

public class HttpSession
extends java.lang.Object

The Class HttpSession defines the data that is stored regarding an existing HTTP session on a particular site.

The session can be invalidated and should only be used while it is valid.

matchesToken

public boolean matchesToken(java.lang.String tokenName,
                            java.net.HttpCookie cookie)
Checks if a particular cookie has the same value as one of the token values in the HTTP session. If the cookie parameter is null, the session matches the token if it does not have a value for the corresponding token.
